#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn48.50"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.50:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.50:0.2"
msgid "5. Jarāvagga "
msgstr "5. Old Age "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 50. Āpaṇasutta → saddha (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.50:0.3"
msgid "50. Āpaṇasutta "
msgstr "50. At Āpaṇa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn48.50:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn48.50:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅgesu viharati āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅgānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Aṅgas, near the Aṅgan town called Āpaṇa. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ekantagato → ekantigato (si)
msgctxt "sn48.50:1.4"
msgid "“yo so, sāriputta, ariyasāvako tathāgate ekantagato abhippasanno, na so tathāgate vā tathāgatasāsane vā kaṅkheyya vā vicikiccheyya vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, would a noble disciple who is sure and devoted to the Realized One have any doubt or uncertainty about the Realized One or his instructions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn48.50:2.1"
msgid "“Yo so, bhante, ariyasāvako tathāgate ekantagato abhippasanno, na so tathāgate vā tathāgatasāsane vā kaṅkheyya vā vicikiccheyya vā. "
msgstr "“Sir, a noble disciple who is sure and devoted to the Realized One would have no doubt or uncertainty about the Realized One or his instructions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.50:2.2"
msgid "saddhassa hi, bhante, ariyasāvakassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ āraddhavīriyo viharissati—akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "You can expect that a faithful noble disciple will live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:2.3"
msgid "Yaṃ hissa, bhante, vīriyaṃ tadassa vīriyindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "For their energy is the faculty of energy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn48.50:3.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, bhante, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ satimā bhavissati, paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā. "
msgstr "You can expect that a faithful and energetic noble disciple will be mindful, with utmost mindfulness and alertness, able to remember and recall what was said and done long ago. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:3.2"
msgid "Yā hissa, bhante, sati tadassa satindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "For their mindfulness is the faculty of mindfulness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn48.50:4.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, bhante, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa upaṭṭhitassatino etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ vossaggārammaṇaṃ karitvā labhissati samādhiṃ, labhissati cittassa ekaggataṃ. "
msgstr "You can expect that a faithful, energetic, and mindful noble disciple will, relying on letting go, gain immersion, gain unification of mind. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:4.2"
msgid "Yo hissa, bhante, samādhi tadassa samādhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "For their samādhi is the faculty of immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.226, sc5
msgctxt "sn48.50:5.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, bhante, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa upaṭṭhitassatino samāhitacittassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ evaṃ pajānissati—"
msgstr "You can expect that a faithful, energetic, mindful noble disciple with their mind immersed in samādhi will understand this: "

msgctxt "sn48.50:5.2"
msgid "anamataggo kho saṃsāro. "
msgstr "‘Transmigration has no known beginning. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:5.3"
msgid "Pubbakoṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ. "
msgstr "No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving. "

msgctxt "sn48.50:5.4"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva tamokāyassa asesavirāganirodho santametaṃ padaṃ paṇītametaṃ padaṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "But when that dark mass of ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, that state is peaceful and sublime. "

#. VAR: nibbānaṃ → nibbānanti (?)
msgctxt "sn48.50:5.5"
msgid "sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr "That is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.50:5.6"
msgid "Yā hissa, bhante, paññā tadassa paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "For their noble wisdom is the faculty of wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: Saddho so → sa kho so (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn48.50:6.1"
msgid "Saddho so, bhante, ariyasāvako evaṃ padahitvā padahitvā evaṃ saritvā saritvā evaṃ samādahitvā samādahitvā evaṃ pajānitvā pajānitvā evaṃ abhisaddahati: "
msgstr "When a noble disciple has tried again and again, recollected again and again, entered immersion again and again, and understood with wisdom again and again, they will be confident of this: "

#. VAR: sutavā → sutāva (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn48.50:6.2"
msgid "‘ime kho te dhammā ye me pubbe sutavā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "‘I have previously heard of these things. "

#. VAR: phusitvā → phassitvā (si)
#. VAR: ativijjha → paṭivijjha (mr)
msgctxt "sn48.50:6.3"
msgid "Tenāhaṃ etarahi kāyena ca phusitvā viharāmi, paññāya ca ativijjha passāmī’ti. "
msgstr "But now I have direct meditative experience of them, and see them with penetrating wisdom.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.50:6.4"
msgid "Yā hissa, bhante, saddhā tadassa saddhindriyan”ti. "
msgstr "For their faith is the faculty of faith.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn48.50:7.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.50:7.2"
msgid "Yo so, sāriputta, ariyasāvako tathāgate ekantagato abhippasanno, na so tathāgate vā tathāgatasāsane vā kaṅkheyya vā vicikiccheyya vā. "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, a noble disciple who is sure and devoted to the Realized One would have no doubt or uncertainty about the Realized One or his instructions. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.50:7.3"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, sāriputta, ariyasāvakassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ āraddhavīriyo viharissati—"
msgstr "(The Buddha then repeated Sāriputta’s answer word for word.) "

msgctxt "sn48.50:7.4"
msgid "akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:7.5"
msgid "Yaṃ hissa, sāriputta, vīriyaṃ tadassa vīriyindriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn48.50:8.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, sāriputta, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ satimā bhavissati, paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:8.2"
msgid "Yā hissa, sāriputta, sati tadassa satindriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn48.50:9.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, sāriputta, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa upaṭṭhitassatino etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ vossaggārammaṇaṃ karitvā labhissati samādhiṃ, labhissati cittassa ekaggataṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:9.2"
msgid "Yo hissa, sāriputta, samādhi tadassa samādhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn48.50:10.1"
msgid "Saddhassa hi, sāriputta, ariyasāvakassa āraddhavīriyassa upaṭṭhitassatino samāhitacittassa etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yaṃ evaṃ pajānissati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:10.2"
msgid "anamataggo kho saṃsāro. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:10.3"
msgid "Pubbakoṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:10.4"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva tamokāyassa asesavirāganirodho santametaṃ padaṃ paṇītametaṃ padaṃ, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:10.5"
msgid "sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:10.6"
msgid "Yā hissa, sāriputta, paññā tadassa paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.227, sc11
#. VAR: Saddho so → sa kho so (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn48.50:11.1"
msgid "Saddho so, sāriputta, ariyasāvako evaṃ padahitvā padahitvā evaṃ saritvā saritvā evaṃ samādahitvā samādahitvā evaṃ pajānitvā pajānitvā evaṃ abhisaddahati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:11.2"
msgid "‘ime kho te dhammā ye me pubbe sutavā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: ativijjha → paṭivijjha (mr)
msgctxt "sn48.50:11.3"
msgid "Tenāhaṃ etarahi kāyena ca phusitvā viharāmi, paññāya ca ativijjha passāmī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn48.50:11.4"
msgid "Yā hissa, sāriputta, saddhā tadassa saddhindriyan”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.50:11.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

